    <p class="post-info">Par <a href="http://standblog.org/">Tristan</a>    le vendredi 20 juin 2008, 19:43        </p>
    
    
    
          <div class="post-content"><p><a href="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3240/2595935836_cffda14016_b.jpg"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3240/2595935836_cffda14016.jpg" alt="Getting ready for celebrating Firefox 3 in the Paris office :-" />)</a></p>


<p><em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2595935836/">Getting ready for celebrating Firefox 3 in the Paris office <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/smile.png" alt=":-)" class="smiley" /></a></em></p>


<p>Avant d'aller m'?crouler chez moi, suite ? quelques semaines de stress entrecoup?es de courtes nuits... (non, je ne vais pas m'?crouler suite au champagne&nbsp;: d'abord j'aime pas ?a, et ensuite on l'a bu avant-hier <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/smile.png" alt=":-)" class="smiley" /> )</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://linuxfr.org/2008/06/18/24225.html" hreflang="fr">Wine 1.0 est sorti</a>, un peu ?clips? par la sortie de Firefox 3&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://computerworld.com/action/article.do?command=viewArticleBasic&amp;articleId=9099178" hreflang="en">Want XP on a new Dell? You'll pay up to $50 extra for the aging OS</a>&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://arstechnica.com/news.ars/post/20080618-microsoft-does-180-will-continue-to-support-msn-music-drm.html" hreflang="en">Microsoft does 180, will continue to support MSN Music DRM</a>. Il y a des jours o? j'ai du mal ? comprendre la strat?gie de MS...&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://tech.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=08/06/20/137216" hreflang="en">ODF a clairement gagn? la bataille des standards</a>, explique un employ? Microsoft, qui doit maintenant chercher un boulot, j'imagine <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/wink.png" alt=";-)" class="smiley" /></li>
<li><a href="http://ambermac.com/articles/2008/06/18/firefox-3-in-5-words-or-less" hreflang="en">5 mots pour d?crire Firefox</a>. Mike Shaver: "Holy crap, we shipped it!". J'en pleure de rire&nbsp;! Variantes&nbsp;:
<ul>
<li>Faster and uses less RAM</li>
<li>Giving bloggers a big hug <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/smile.png" alt=":-)" class="smiley" /></li>
<li>Best browsing experience. Ever!</li>
<li>Super-delicious Open-Source awesomeness</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Bertrand Lemaire voit une <a href="http://www.bertrandlemaire.com/dotclear/index.php?2008/06/19/995-la-france-bat-l-italie-les-pays-bas-et-la-roumanie" hreflang="fr">corr?lation inverse entre niveau footballistique et t?l?chargements de Firefox</a>, et <a href="http://www.bashfr.org/?7426" hreflang="fr">BashFR enfonce le clou</a> (via <a href="http://twitter.com/aurelienbardon/" hreflang="en">Aur?lien</a>)&nbsp;!</li>
<li><a href="http://www.tux-planet.fr/revenus-et-audience-de-la-blogsphere-francophone-etat-des-lieux-2008/" hreflang="fr">Revenus et audience de la blogosph?re francophone</a>, ou la preuve du manque ? gagner en ne mettant pas de pub sur le Standblog. (1500 EUR par mois pour <a href="http://www.2803.com/about/" hreflang="fr">Henri Labarre</a>, pourtant derri?re moi au <a href="http://www.wikio.fr/blogs/top/high-tech" hreflang="fr">classement Wikio High-Tech</a>, ou <a href="http://www.presse-citron.net/" hreflang="fr">Eric de Presse-Citron</a> qui vient d'annoncer qu'il passait <a href="http://www.presse-citron.net/revelation-de-la-semaine-jai-trouve-un-travail" hreflang="fr">blogueur pro</a> ? 3500 EUR par mois). On remarquera que les blogs sans pub dans le top Wikio sont rares, ? part <a href="http://www.fredcavazza.net/" hreflang="fr">Fred Cavazza</a> et <a href="http://www.kelblog.com/" hreflang="fr">Pierre Chappaz</a> (mais financi?rement, Pierre ne joue pas dans la m?me court que Fred et moi :-D), et ceux parlant de logiciels Libres et des standards le sont encore plus :-(&nbsp;;</li>
<li>Le Seneca College vient de publier le <a href="http://zenit.senecac.on.ca/wiki/index.php/Mozilla_Developer_Resource_Kit" hreflang="en">Mozilla Developer Resource Kit</a> qui comprend <a href="http://zenit.senecac.on.ca/wiki/dxr/" hreflang="en">DXR</a>, et c'est (tr?s) beau. <a href="http://xulfr.org/news/2008/06/20/254-mozilla-developer-resource-kit-et-dxr" hreflang="fr">Laurent Jouanneau explique pourquoi</a>&nbsp;;</li>
<li>Un poign?e de billets int?ressants&nbsp;:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://eaves.ca/2008/06/10/the-open-web-is-a-social-movement/" hreflang="en">The Open Web is a social movement</a>&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://commonspace.typepad.com/commonspace/2008/06/the-next-million-mozillians.html" hreflang="en">The Next Million Mozillians</a>&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://blog.lizardwrangler.com/2008/06/17/firefox-3-tip-of-the-iceberg-2/" hreflang="en">Firefox 3 ? Tip of the Iceberg</a>&nbsp;;</li>
<li><a href="http://blog.lizardwrangler.com/" hreflang="en">Mozilla and the OECD in Seoul</a>. "Part of our dream for Mozilla has been to be a voice for the health of the Internet itself. To use our technology, our products and our community process to demonstrate what is possible, and to help others see that openness, participation and distributed decision-making can lead to many positive developments. Mozilla?s participation in events such as this OECD meeting demonstrates that we are doing this. We represent a new style of development for Internet product and the Internet experience."&nbsp;;</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>

<p>Je manque terriblement d'?nergie pour rebondir sur ces derniers billets et pourtant, c'est un sujet qui le m?rite. Bon, je reprends des forces, je fais une <a href="http://www.kiberpipa.org/firefox/" hreflang="en">conf?rence ? Ljubljana, Slov?nie</a>, on fait la f?te ? Paris pour la sortie de Firefox 3, je prends une semaine de vacances et c'est parti pour un tour&nbsp;! <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/laugh.png" alt=":-D" class="smiley" /></p></div>
    
          <p class="post-info-co">
              <a href="http://standblog.org/blog/post/2008/06/20/En-vrac-lauteur-et-le-billet#comments" class="comment_count">12 commentaires</a>
                      </p>
        </div>
    
          <div class="post odd ">

    <p class="day-date">jeudi 19 juin 2008</p>    
    <h2 id="p3555" class="post-title"><a
    href="http://standblog.org/blog/post/2008/06/19/Firefox-3-launch-press-coverage">Firefox 3 launch press coverage</a></h2>
    
    <p class="post-info">Par <a href="http://standblog.org/">Tristan</a>    le jeudi 19 juin 2008, 14:18        - <a href="http://standblog.org/blog/category/En">en</a>
        </p>
    
    
    
          <div class="post-content"><p>With more than <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592547876/" hreflang="en">8 million downloads</a>, the <a href="http://www.spreadfirefox.com/en-US/worldrecord" hreflang="en">Download Day</a> is an amazing success. <a href="" hreflang="en">Firefox 3 market share</a>, measured in real time by Net Applications is North of 6%, just 36 hours after the launch. But besides download numbers, the idea of setting a Guinness book record was immensely effective to get the word out. It was super effective in mobilizing our 180 million users and the members of the press. Press coverage has been amazing in all countries, including <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592624716/">US&amp;UK</a>, <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592547768/">France</a>, <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592547660/">Italy</a>, <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592547622/">Germany</a> and <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2592547708/">Spain</a> (there is no Google News in Poland). <strong>Not only the coverage is beyond amazing, it has also enabled Mozilla to reach a new level in terms of Open-Source visibility for itself, for the Mozilla Manifesto (our all of our values) and for the whole Open-Source / Free Software world.</strong> For all these reasons, I'm super proud to be part of it. Thanks <del>a</del> 8.3 million to all of you who have made this possible. To <a href="http://blog.mozilla.com/schrep/2008/06/18/whats-next-after-firefox-3/" hreflang="en">quote Schrep</a>:</p>


<blockquote><p>If you've filed a bug, translated a string, written code, worked on an add-on, supported the development infrastructure, or helped to explain Firefox to someone else, <strong>you</strong> were part of making Firefox 3 a success.</p></blockquote>


<p>But back to the topic I wanted to address, with a very short list of big media that have published content about Firefox<sup>[<a href="#pnote-3555-1" id="rev-pnote-3555-1">1</a>]</sup>:</p>



