    <h2 id="p3553" class="post-title"><a
    href="http://standblog.org/blog/post/2008/06/18/I-hear-servers-screeching">I hear servers screeching!</a></h2>
    
    <p class="post-info">Par <a href="http://standblog.org/">Tristan</a>    le mercredi 18 juin 2008, 15:05        - <a href="http://standblog.org/blog/category/En">en</a>
        </p>
    
    
    
          <div class="post-content"><p>The demand for the new Firefox 3 browser has been simply overwhelming. As I write this, the number of downloads is at <a href="http://downloadcounter.sj.mozilla.com/">6.5 million</a> (with around 6000 new downloads taking place every minute) so we are well on the way to breaking the Guinness World Record (Firefox 2 was downloaded 1.6 million times on the first day in October 2006).</p>


<p>This is great recognition for our community of developers, testers and localisers who have worked so hard to make Mozilla what it is today.</p>


<p>We did experience a small outage on the Mozilla download site last night when Firefox 3 officially launched; as noted on some news sites including <a href="http://www.theregister.co.uk/2008/06/17/firefox_3_debuts/">The Register</a> and <a href="http://blogs.guardian.co.uk/technology/2008/06/17/get_firefox_sorry_you_cant.html">The Guardian</a>.  But I think this just demonstrates the huge success and high demand from consumers who want a better and more personalised browsing experience.</p>


<p>More good news? Because of the slight delay at the start of the Download Day, we have pushed back the cut off time to break the number of downloads in a 24 hour period!  The new end date and time is 20.16 hours (CET) June 18th 2008.</p>


<p>To take advantage and be part of a new Guinness World Record, you can download the Mozilla Firefox 3 browser at <a href="http://getfirefox.com/">GetFirefox.com</a>.</p>


<p>Still not sure if Firefox 3 is for you? Check out <a href="http://news.sky.com/skynews/article/0,,91221-1319341,00.html">the Firefox 3 demo over at Sky News</a>!</p></div>
    
          <p class="post-info-co">
              <a href="http://standblog.org/blog/post/2008/06/18/I-hear-servers-screeching#comments" class="comment_count">14 commentaires</a>
