    <h2 id="p3534" class="post-title"><a
    href="http://standblog.org/blog/post/2008/06/08/Firefox-on-video-in-Italy">Firefox on video in Italy!</a></h2>
    
    <p class="post-info">Par <a href="http://standblog.org/">Tristan</a>    le dimanche  8 juin 2008, 10:23        - <a href="http://standblog.org/blog/category/En">en</a>
        </p>
    
        <ul class="post-tags">    <li><a href="http://standblog.org/blog/tag/fx3">fx3</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://standblog.org/blog/tag/italy">italy</a></li>
    </ul>    
    
          <div class="post-content"><p><a href="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3187/2559975865_0cfaba3e69_o.png"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3187/2559975865_0cfaba3e69_o.png" alt="Giuliano on Adnkronos" /></a></p>


<p><em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nitot/2559975865/">Giuliano talking about Firefox 3 on Adnkronos</a></em></p>


<p><a href="http://www.adnkronos.com/IGN/Video/?vid=1.0.2211931233" hreflang="it">Giuliano and Schrep demoing Firefox in Milan</a>.</p>


<p>It's amazing how talking in Italian makes a great product even sexier <img src="/dotclear2/themes/default/smilies/wink.png" alt=";-)" class="smiley" /></p>


<p>(Schrep is the ever traveling VP of Engineering and Giuliano is one of our volunteers in Italy, leading the very dynamic <a href="http://www.mozillaitalia.it/" hreflang="it">Mozilla Italia</a> community, who manages localization and local support).</p></div>
    
